Federation de International Football Association (FIFA) has approved the Stephen Okechukwu Keshi Stadium for the upcoming International friendly between the Super Eagles of Nigeria and the Cranes of Uganda in Asaba,National Daily learnt.

Following the approval from FIFA, the stadium will now officially host its first international match which would be between the Nigerian Super Eagles and Ugandan Cranes.

The last time The Super Eagles faced the Cranes was at the Godswill Akpabio Stadium, Uyo where the Super Eagles were victorious by a lone goal and Vincent Enyeama was in goal and captained the Super Eagles for that encounter.
